	<h1>Ajay Patil</h1>
	<p>Ajay Patil, co-founder and partner of Showcall Inc. , started in the production business over 20 years ago. Patil has a varied skill set that he has developed over the years working as a talent buyer; booking national acts, producing his own concerts, serving as a tour manager and lighting director on a number of rock and roll tours and finally by entering the special event industry as a sales executive/technical producer.</p>
	<p>Patil spent almost 7 years at Current Events International (CEI), where aside from eventually becoming Vice President of Business Development, he also played a key role in producing a number of large political and corporate events, including serving as the Technical Vendor Liaison for the 54th Presidential Inauguration.</p>
	<p>In 2001, Patil co-founded Showcall with A. Blayne Candy and has spent the last several years growing the company and producing a variety of high profile, large format events such as Pope Benedict XVI’s Mass for 47,000 at Nationals Stadium, the G20 Summit in DC and Pittsburgh, the Annapolis Mideast Peace Conference and the White House Conference on the Americas. Most recently Patil led the charge on the launch of Showcall’s newest division that focuses on event security assets, by supporting the United States Secret Service on their efforts in securing the 56th Presidential Inauguration and the G20 Summit in Pittsburgh. Patil also has maintained his entertainment background, as he has served as Tour Manager for the B52’s Summer 2003 and 2004 Tours.</p>
